A wage strike by South African Revenue Service workers has forced the closure of around 40 branches. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A wage strike by South African Revenue Service workers has forced the closure of around 40 branches. Nehawu and the Public Servants Association are calling for the revenue collector to come back to the negotiating table with an offer higher than 1.39 percent. READ: Mass action forces SARS branches to close The unions say the strike will continue indefinitely if their demands aren't met. The  PSA and Nehawu began striking in May, demanding increases of around 12 percent. READ: SARS strike | Taxpayers urged to use digital platforms SARS meanwhile says it doesn't have the funds for this. It is urging the public to continue making use of its digital services.